-- Ferrer Wins First Set of U.S. Open Men’s Semifinal From Djokovic
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-09-09T15:24:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-09/ferrer-wins-first-set-of-u-s-open-men-s-semifinal-from-djokovic.html
Fourth-seeded  David Ferrer  of Spain
finished off the first set of his semifinal against defending
champion Novak Djokovic of Serbia, winning the first game of
today’s play to win the set 6-2.  The match was halted yesterday by the threat of severe
weather and resumed this morning with Ferrer leading 5-2 at the
National Tennis Center in new York.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  